                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ḥusaynī-Shāhī</title>
                     <note>Flyleaf, recto: Presented by Sir John Malcolm May 19 - 1827. Flyleaf, verso: no: 22. J.L Folio one, recto: Note on Durrani history, possibly by Malcolm. Contains a loose piece of paper with writing. A history of the Durrani Afghans from Ahmad Shah to A.H. 1212. Husain-Shahi is the title given in the author's preface. Tarikh i Nasab Namah i Ahmad Shah Durrani Afghani appears on the first flyleaf, recto and on a slip pasted on the front cover. Headings and puntuation in red. Ruled margins. Panel of illumination at beginning.</note>
                     <incipit>Hamd i bi-hadd wa thana yi bi-'add sazawar i padshahi ast</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, p. 399.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, iii, pp. 904-5.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No 588.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Malcolm's gift is described in the Donations Register for 19 May 1827 and in the Transactions for 1830, pp. xcix-c.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
